<div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">
  <h1>🚀 Rails MVC Flow Demo</h1>
  <p><strong><%= @message %></strong></p>
  <p>Current time: <%= @current_time %></p>

  <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 20px 0;">
    <h2>Understanding Rails MVC Flow:</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Route</strong> - Maps URL to controller action (config/routes.rb)</li>
      <li><strong>Controller</strong> - Processes request, prepares data (app/controllers/)</li>
      <li><strong>View</strong> - Displays data to user (app/views/)</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <h2>Try These Demo Buttons:</h2>

  <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; margin: 20px 0;">
    <%= link_to "👋 Hello Demo", hello_path,
        class: "btn",
        style: "background-color: #007bff; color: white; padding: 10px 20px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 5px; display: inline-block;" %>

    <%= link_to "🔢 Counter Demo", counter_path(count: 0),
        class: "btn",
        style: "background-color: #28a745; color: white; padding: 10px 20px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 5px; display: inline-block;" %>

    <%= link_to "📝 Form Demo", form_demo_path,
        class: "btn",
        style: "background-color: #ffc107; color: black; padding: 10px 20px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 5px; display: inline-block;" %>
  </div>

  <div style="background-color: #e9ecef; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 20px 0;">
    <h3>🔍 What happens when you click a button:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Browser</strong> sends request to Rails server</li>
      <li><strong>Router</strong> matches URL to controller action</li>
      <li><strong>Controller</strong> processes request and sets instance variables</li>
      <li><strong>View</strong> renders HTML using those variables</li>
      <li><strong>Response</strong> is sent back to browser</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>